
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `licensecheck` baraye barresi va taeen nooe mojavez (license) file-ha dar yek projeh ya directory estefade mishavad.  In dastoor komak mikonad ta az ehtemal vojood mojavez-haye motenaqez ya gheir motabegh ba siyaasat-haye sherkati agah shavid.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `licensecheck .`  -->  📂 Barresi hame file-ha dar directory فعلی (fe'li)
    🔹 `licensecheck -r`  -->  🔄 Barresi rekursiv (recursive) dar hameye زیرپوشه‌ها (zirpooshe-ha)
    🔹 `licensecheck -f <format>`  -->  📊 Namayesh natije be formathaaye mokhtalef (mesl CSV, JSON)
    🔹 `licensecheck -n`  --> 🚫 Faghat namayesh file-haee ke mojavez-e moshkel darand.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ licensecheck .

    🔹 Barresi mojavez-haye hameye file-ha dar directory فعلی (fe'li).

    $ licensecheck -r

    🔹 Barresi rekursiv (recursive) dar hameye directory-ha va zirpooshe-ha.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ licensecheck -n .

    🔹 Faghat file-haee ra namayesh midahad ke ba mojavez-haye نامشخص (namoshakhas) ya moshkeldar mark shodeand.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `licensecheck` command is used to scan files for license information in a project or directory. It helps identify potential licensing conflicts or non-compliant files based on company policies.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `licensecheck .`  -->  📂 Scan all files in the current directory.
    🔹 `licensecheck -r`  -->  🔄 Scan recursively through all subdirectories.
    🔹 `licensecheck -f <format>`  -->  📊 Output results in different formats (e.g., CSV, JSON).
    🔹 `licensecheck -n`  --> 🚫 Only show files with problematic licenses.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ licensecheck .

    🔹 Scan all files in the current directory for licenses.

    $ licensecheck -r

    🔹 Recursively scan all files and subdirectories for licenses.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ licensecheck -n .

    🔹 Shows only those files that are flagged as having unclear or problematic licenses.
